---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Israel Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/israel/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Cyprus for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/cyprus' },
  { title: 'Greece for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/greece' },
  { title: 'UAE for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/uae' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'israelFit', header: 'Israel Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'ILS$2,700-3,855/mo', israelFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'ILS$3,160-4,515/mo', israelFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'ILS$2,430-3,470/mo', israelFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'ILS$2,260-3,225/mo', israelFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Local (Clalit, Maccabi)', entryAge: 'Varies', renewal: 'Annual', monthlyFrom: 'ILS$500-1,500/mo', israelFit: 'For residents' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'ILS$2,430-3,855', annual: 'ILS$29.2K-46.3K' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'ILS$3,335-5,140', annual: 'ILS$40K-61.7K' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'ILS$4,480-6,900', annual: 'ILS$53.8K-82.8K' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Visit', monthly: 'ILS$400-1,000/visit', annual: 'Moderate' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Stay', monthly: 'ILS$3,000-8,000/day', annual: 'Per incident' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Israel 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Israel. World-class healthcare, Mediterranean climate, innovation hub, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Israel"
  subheadline="Israel offers world-class healthcare, Mediterranean beaches, holy sites, innovation culture, and vibrant lifestyle—a modern nation with ancient roots and excellent medical facilities."
  heroImage="/images/countries/israel-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Israel</h2>
  <p>
    Israel offers world-class healthcare, Mediterranean climate, holy sites for multiple religions, innovation culture, and vibrant modern society. For Jewish retirees with Law of Return eligibility or those seeking excellent healthcare with cultural depth, Israel provides unique combination.
  </p>

  <p>
    Tel Aviv offers secular lifestyle and beaches. Jerusalem has religious significance and history. Haifa provides quiet Mediterranean living. Netanya has beach community. Eilat offers year-round warmth. Most Western expats choose Tel Aviv area for lifestyle.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> World-class; universal for residents</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Hebrew; English widely spoken</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> ILS$8,000-15,000/month (~$2,200-4,100 USD); expensive</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Mediterranean; warm; dry summers</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Innovative; diverse; intense</li>
      <li><strong>Law of Return:</strong> Citizenship for Jews</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Israel Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Israel has world-class healthcare—universal coverage for residents through four HMOs (Clalit, Maccabi, Leumit, Meuhedet). Excellent hospitals including Hadassah, Ichilov, Sheba. Medical innovation hub. Non-residents need private coverage. Medical tourism attracts visitors from around world.
  </p>

  <p>
    Residents (citizens/permanent) have excellent public coverage. Non-residents need international insurance. Healthcare quality among world's best. High life expectancy (82+ years) reflects healthcare quality.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">World-Class Healthcare</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Israel has excellent healthcare—universal coverage for residents, world-class hospitals, medical innovation. Non-residents need private coverage. If eligible for Law of Return, healthcare comes with citizenship. Otherwise, international insurance required.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Israel has specific immigration pathways:
  </p>

  <h3>Law of Return (Aliyah)</h3>
  <p>
    Jews (including those with Jewish parent/grandparent or married to Jews) can make Aliyah and receive citizenship. Includes healthcare access. Primary pathway for Jewish retirees.
  </p>

  <h3>Tourist Visa</h3>
  <p>
    90 days visa-free for many nationalities. Extensions possible but limited.
  </p>

  <h3>A/1 Temporary Residence</h3>
  <p>
    For specific circumstances. Not general retirement visa. Limited options for non-Jews.
  </p>

  <h3>Expert/Specialist Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For those with special skills. Some semi-retired professionals use this route.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements depend on status:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Olim (new citizens):</strong> Universal coverage after Aliyah</li>
    <li><strong>Tourists:</strong> Travel insurance required</li>
    <li><strong>Non-residents:</strong> International coverage essential</li>
    <li><strong>Practical:</strong> International coverage for non-citizens</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Israel</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      For non-citizen residents: international insurance essential as no universal coverage access. For citizens through Aliyah: excellent universal coverage, may want supplemental private insurance. Healthcare quality excellent either way.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Israel without citizenship:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Israel</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Middle East network</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>Local quality:</strong> World-class hospitals available</li>
    <li><strong>Aliyah route:</strong> Citizenship brings universal coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage for Israel (non-citizens).</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Israel (ILS ~3.65 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Aliyah:</strong> Citizenship brings universal coverage</li>
    <li><strong>HMO supplemental:</strong> For citizens needing extra coverage</li>
    <li><strong>High deductible:</strong> Local care excellent</li>
    <li><strong>Regional plans:</strong> Middle East focused</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Oleh, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $3,500/month pension. Made Aliyah. Tel Aviv.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Israeli HMO (Maccabi) + supplemental private.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~ILS$800/month (~$220) supplemental. Universal base; private upgrade.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Christian Pilgrim Retiree, 70</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,800/month pension. Tourist rotation. Jerusalem.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global comprehensive (non-citizen).</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~ILS$3,800/month (~$1,040). International coverage; excellent local hospitals.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Tech Retiree, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $5,000/month income. Aliyah eligible. Tel Aviv.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Make Aliyah; Israeli HMO + premium supplement.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~ILS$1,000/month (~$275) supplement. Startup culture; full coverage.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What is Law of Return?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Jews (those with Jewish parent, grandparent, or spouse) can become Israeli citizens through Aliyah. Includes universal healthcare access. Major benefit if eligible. Process involves documentation, Hebrew learning, integration support.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Israel safe for retirees?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Complex answer—security situations arise but daily life is safe. Tel Aviv very safe. Jerusalem more complex. Iron Dome provides protection. Security is national priority. Most expats adapt to security awareness. Evaluate current situation.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I need Hebrew?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Helpful but not essential—English widely spoken, especially Tel Aviv. Healthcare accessible in English. Hebrew enriches experience. Olim receive free Hebrew lessons (Ulpan). Many expats manage with English.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Israel expensive?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—one of world's most expensive countries. Tel Aviv particularly costly. Housing, food, services all expensive. Budget $3,000-5,000/month minimum for comfortable life. Not a budget retirement destination.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Israel coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Israeli authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
